<DocsLayout
  title="API Reference - Hovue"
  description="Complete API reference for Hovue icons. Learn about all available props and options."
  prev={{ url: '/docs/quick-start', title: 'Quick Start' }}
  next={{ url: '/docs/animations', title: 'Animation Guide' }}
>
  <h1>API Reference</h1>

  <p>
    This page documents all props and options available for Hovue icons. All icons share the same
    API for consistency.
  </p>

  <h2>Props</h2>

  <h3>size</h3>
  <p><strong>Type:</strong> <code>number | string</code></p>
  <p><strong>Default:</strong> <code>24</code></p>
  <p><strong>Description:</strong> The size of the icon in pixels.</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">:size</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);">"24"</span> /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>color</h3>
  <p><strong>Type:</strong> <code>string</code></p>
  <p><strong>Default:</strong> <code>"currentColor"</code></p>
  <p><strong>Description:</strong> The color of the icon. Accepts any valid CSS color value.</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">color</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);">"#319795"</span
    > /&gt;<br />
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">color</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"rgb(49, 151, 149)"</span
    > /&gt;<br />
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">color</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"currentColor"</span
    > /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>animation</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Type:</strong>
    <code>"slide" | "bounce" | "rotate" | "pulse" | "fade" | "none"</code>
  </p>
  <p><strong>Default:</strong> <code>"none"</code></p>
  <p><strong>Description:</strong> The animation type to apply to the icon.</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"slide"</span
    > /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>animationDuration</h3>
  <p><strong>Type:</strong> <code>number</code></p>
  <p><strong>Default:</strong> <code>300</code></p>
  <p><strong>Description:</strong> The duration of the animation in milliseconds.</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"500"</span
    > /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>strokeWidth</h3>
  <p><strong>Type:</strong> <code>number</code></p>
  <p><strong>Default:</strong> <code>2</code></p>
  <p><strong>Description:</strong> The stroke width of the icon.</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">:stroke-width</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"1.5"</span
    > /&gt;
  </div>

  <h2>Events</h2>

  <h3>@click</h3>
  <p><strong>Type:</strong> <code>MouseEvent</code></p>
  <p><strong>Description:</strong> Emitted when the icon is clicked.</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">@click</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"handleClick"</span
    > /&gt;
  </div>

  <h3>@hover</h3>
  <p><strong>Type:</strong> <code>MouseEvent</code></p>
  <p><strong>Description:</strong> Emitted when the mouse enters the icon.</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>
    <span style="color: var(--pink);">@hover</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);"
      >"handleHover"</span
    > /&gt;
  </div>

  <h2>TypeScript</h2>

  <p>All icons are fully typed. Import the types you need:</p>

  <div class="docs-code">
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">import</span>
    <span style="color: var(--purple);">type</span> &#123; <span style="color: var(--orange);"
      >IconProps</span
    > &#125; <span style="color: var(--purple);">from</span>
    <span style="color: var(--cyan);">'hovue'</span>
  </div>

